  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat the oven to 180°C. Season the chicken breasts generously with salt and pepper, then transfer to a baking tray and cook in the oven for 25 mins. Allow to cool once cooked – the salad doesn’t need to be warm."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring a pan of water to the boil, then drop in the green beans and blanch for 2-3 mins."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Put the cooked green beans, mangetout, cooked chicken breasts, mango and most of the coriander onto a chopping board. Chop into even-sized pieces. Add most of the peanuts to the board and chop again. Add all of your chopped ingredients to a large bowl."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "For the dressing, squeeze the juice from your lime into a bowl. Finely chop the chilli and add that, too. Grate in the garlic, then add the remaining dressing ingredients."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour the dressing into the chopped salad bowl and toss together. Garnish with the reserved coriander and the reserved peanuts. Enjoy."
    }
  ],
